    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nWith the following config after exiting from new window events `BufLeave/BufInsert` does not trigger.\r\nI guess the problem is in create_autocmd \"InsertLeave\", if trigger \":lua CLOSE_WINDOW()\" manually it works as expected\r\n```\r\nlocal api = vim.api\r\n\r\nlocal winid = nil\r\nlocal buf = nil\r\n\r\nfunction CREATE_WINDOW()\r\n\tbuf = api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\r\n\r\n\twinid = api.nvim_open_win(\r\n\t\tbuf,\r\n\t\ttrue,\r\n\t\t{ col = 1, row = 0, width = 10, border = \"none\", height = 1, relative = \"cursor\", style = \"minimal\" }\r\n\t)\r\n\r\n\tvim.cmd(\"startinsert\")\r\n\r\n\tapi.nvim_create_autocmd(\"InsertLeave\", {\r\n\t\tcallback = CLOSE_WINDOW,\r\n\t\tonce = true,\r\n\t})\r\nend\r\n\r\nfunction CLOSE_WINDOW()\r\n\tif winid then\r\n\t\tapi.nvim_win_close(winid, false)\r\n\t\twinid = nil\r\n\tend\r\nend\r\n\r\napi.nvim_create_autocmd({ \"BufEnter\", \"BufLeave\" }, {\r\n\tcallback = function(opts)\r\n\t\tprint(\"Buf Enter/Leave all\", vim.inspect(opts), api.nvim_get_current_buf(), vim.inspect(api.nvim_list_bufs()))\r\n\tend,\r\n})\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nnvim some_file -nu `following_config.lua`(from description)\r\n`:lua CREATE_WINDOW()`\r\nexit insert mode\r\ncheck messages, you can see one `BufEnter & BufLeave` events, but i think there also should be  another one `BufLeave & BufEnter` after exit window.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nI think there should be 4 triggered events(not 2)\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-43b0e27\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nidk\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nFedora\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nkitty\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nterm256-color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nfrom source",
